com.kuka.geometry.events

Class ObjectStructureEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.geometry.events.TreeEvent
      • com.kuka.geometry.events.TreeStructureEvent
        • com.kuka.geometry.events.ObjectStructureEvent
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ObjectAttachEvent, ObjectDetachEvent

    public abstract class ObjectStructureEvent
extends TreeStructureEvent
    Event which indicates that the structure of objects within a monitored tree was changed.

    The event is fired each time an object is attached to or removed from the tree.

    See Also:
    ObjectAttachEvent, ObjectDetachEvent

                            SpatialObject oldParentObject,
                            SpatialObject newParentObject,
                            ObjectFrame oldParentObjectFrame,
                            ObjectFrame newParentObjectFrame)
        Creates an event which informs about changes to the object structure of a tree.
        Parameters:
        object - the object which was attached to or removed from the tree
        oldParentObject - the former parent object of the attached or detached object, or null if not known
        newParentObject - the new parent object of the attached or detached object, or null if not known
        oldParentObjectFrame - the former parent object frame of the attached object, or null if not known
        newParentObjectFrame - the new parent object frame of the attached or detached object, or null if not known
